# Project Base Rules

- Use `AGENTS.md` as the canonical repository entrypoint.
- Use `docs/ai/README.md` as the detailed system of record.
- Read `docs/ai/context-profiles.md` before loading deep guidance.
- When the repository is new or the structure is still fluid, read `docs/ai/start-bootstrap.md` first.
- When the repository already exists or migration is involved, read `docs/ai/start-adoption.md` first.
- Fix `projectFamily`, `projectNature`, and `runtimeRole[]` before finalizing major structure.
- Confirm core roles first and add extended roles only when needed.
- Use `docs/ai/project-generation-spec.md`, `docs/ai/project-family-map.md`, and `docs/ai/project-selection-mapping.md` when bootstrapping or reshaping a repository.
- Use `docs/ai/stack-matrix.md` before changing language, framework, runtime, or build defaults.
- Follow the nearest existing pattern before introducing new structure.
- Keep changes scoped to the request.
- Do not commit secrets, tokens, production credentials, or real chat IDs.
- Prefer backward-compatible changes for API and DB work.
- Update docs when code, config, DB, validation, or rollout behavior changes.
- If stack defaults are overridden, record the exception in repo-local overlay docs.
- Run at least one relevant verification step before completion.
